div.p:
1. It has been the endeavour of Satan from the beginning of the world to put asunder what God had joined together;
See Matt. 19:6; Mark 10:9. to separate inward from outward religion; to set one of these at variance with the other. And herein he has met with no small success among those who were ‘ignorant of his devices’.
2 Cor. 2:11. Cf. No. 42, ‘Satan’s Devices’.
